1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,600
Is there anything I can help with?

2
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:09,759
I need something physical to destress.

3
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:12,760
This is Pun.
He's my cousin, my uncle's son.

4
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,720
Nice to meet you.

5
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:17,320
<i>You really have to go</i>
<i>to Mae Hong Son for this project?</i>

6
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,840
<i>Can't you do it somewhere closer?</i>

7
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,440
Driver!

8
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,560
Please pull over!

9
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:25,400
Here comes that rascal, my nephew.

10
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,800
Win!

11
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,600
Over here!

12
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:33,960
<i>Don't be so formal. Just call me Win.</i>

13
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,400
Nice to meet you, Win.

14
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,560
Nice to meet you, Pie.

15
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,960
<i>Why does he keep talking about Pie?</i>

16
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,640
Does he have feelings for her?

17
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,960
Double Rainbow, that's a bad omen!

18
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:44,920
What bad omen?

19
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,880
A double rainbow means love.

20
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,960
It's so beautiful.

21
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,160
There's a rose garden here too?

22
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:09,120
One, two.

23
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,200
Quick!

24
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:46,280
Thanks so much for helping me
pick up the papers earlier.

25
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:49,040
If it weren't for you,
I'd have to bother the villagers again.

26
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,720
No need to thank me.

27
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,160
I just wanted to help the villagers.

28
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,120
Are you messing with me?

29
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,240
I'm serious.

30
00:03:57,840 --> 00:04:01,080
Maybe next election,
I'll run for parliament in this district.

31
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,280
Run for parliament?

32
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:06,720
Come on.

33
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,640
Thanks.

34
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,520
Pie, wait.

35
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,160
Don't go yet.

36
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:39,920
But it's getting dark.

37
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,800
I know.

38
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:43,320
But we can't go back yet.

39
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,840
The tire's flat.

40
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,520
Oh, you're right.

41
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,560
It's completely flat.
Win, what should we do?

42
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,200
Do you have a tire pump?

43
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:02,840
No. My dad took it with him in the car.

44
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,920
Should we try walking back?

45
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,120
Better not.

46
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:12,280
It's dark already, and it's dangerous.

47
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,680
You should stay here for the night

48
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,080
and head back in the morning.

49
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,840
This is delicious. What's it called?

50
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,360
- This?
- Yeah.

51
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,400
It's called Aeb Ong Aw.

52
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,600
Aeb Ong Aw?

53
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,680
Yeah.

54
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,760
"Aeb".

55
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,040
Kind of like steamed curry?

56
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:51,120
Sort of.

57
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:54,360
This Aeb Ong Aw, do you know
what it's made of?

58
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,560
Of course.

59
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,480
Pig brain.

60
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,600
- How did you know?
- What?

61
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,240
Doesn't that gross you out?

62
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:05,720
No. Why would it?

63
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,680
You know, I've wanted
to try this for a long time.

64
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,960
I don't have much time left.

65
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:20,320
I'd rather spend it collecting
as much happiness as I can.

66
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,280
Why?

67
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,400
Do you have some terminal illness?

68
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:33,120
Are you dying?

69
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,200
Are you crazy? No.

70
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:40,960
You're talking like someone
who's about to die.

71
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,920
I'm not dying.

72
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,480
Someone like me doesn't die that easily.

73
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,040
Who knows?

74
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:03,360
People die so easily.

75
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:10,320
You see someone in the morning,

76
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:14,720
and by evening…

77
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,320
they're gone.

78
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,600
Like they never even existed.

79
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,640
You mean…

80
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,000
your parents, right?

81
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,440
I'm sorry.

82
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,920
I didn't think before I spoke.

83
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,960
I'm sorry.

84
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,840
I never knew

85
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:58,160
my family was tens of millions in debt.

86
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:03,120
After I finished arranging the funeral

87
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,200
and clearing the debts,

88
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,360
that's when I found out the truth.

89
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,440
I regret it.

90
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,800
If my parents had told me,

91
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:25,120
maybe I could have helped them somehow.

92
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:32,920
But I was still living happily,

93
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:38,520
while they were suffering.

94
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,720
My parents divorced a long time ago.

95
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,400
My dad has a new family now.

96
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:21,280
He actually wanted me to live with him.

97
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,120
But I felt sorry for Mom.

98
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:30,080
If I left her too,

99
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,040
she'd totally lose it.

100
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,000
Honestly, I understand

101
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,680
why Dad left.

102
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:52,120
My mom

103
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,200
likes to control everything.

104
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,680
Now that I'm the only one she has left,

105
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,440
she controls me even more.

106
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,240
Feeling suffocated?

107
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,080
I'm used to it.

108
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:20,120
I know she does it

109
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:23,600
out of love, because she worries about me.

110
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,400
Come to think of it,

111
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,480
our parents are kind of the same.

112
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:42,200
Sometimes love that's too much

113
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,560
can hurt their children too.

114
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:53,520
That's true.

115
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,440
That's the way it is.

116
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,280
So,

117
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,960
during these three months I'm here,

118
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:13,920
I'm going to make the most of it.

119
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,080
I'll go wherever I want,
do whatever I want,

120
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:23,040
before I have to go back and live
under my mom's rules forever.

121
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:27,840
You know.

122
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,800
I didn't call her today.

123
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,720
No idea how angry she's going to be.

124
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,960
She's definitely going to explode.

125
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:42,160
Why isn't anyone answering?

126
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,760
Where did Pie go?

127
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:12,720
Where did Win disappear to?

128
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,320
He's not answering the phone.

129
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,040
Hello.

130
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,920
This is Saensuk Homestay.

131
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,640
What are you all doing over there?

132
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:27,040
I've been calling nonstop.
Why aren't you answering?

133
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:30,240
Sorry. Did you dial the wrong number?

134
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:32,680
This is Saensuk Homestay, not your house.

135
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:34,720
Do you think you're talking to a servant?

136
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:35,920
My daughter is your customer.

137
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,680
And I'm her mother.
That makes me your boss.

138
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:40,560
<i>Where is Pie right now?</i>

139
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,840
Is she there? Put her
on the phone immediately.

140
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:43,840
I want to speak to her.

141
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:45,720
- She's not here.
- What?

142
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,240
She's not there? Then where is she?

143
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:51,120
Don't worry. She went out with my nephew.

144
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,080
<i>I assure you, she's well taken care of.</i>

145
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,560
It's perfectly safe.

146
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:56,800
What? She went with your nephew?

147
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:58,640
<i>My daughter can take care of herself.</i>

148
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:03,000
Hey! Tell your nephew
to stay away from my daughter.

149
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:04,480
And don't let any man--

150
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:06,960
Oh my, that's piercing my ears.

151
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,560
Such a temper. So rude.

152
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,960
Are they really mother and daughter?
They're nothing alike.

153
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,480
Hang on.

154
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,800
Where did those two run off to?

155
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,880
TUESDAY, 25 SEPTEMBER

156
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,880
Are you worried about your mom?

157
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:48,440
She's probably worried too.

158
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:53,120
Hey, where are you going?

159
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:58,240
I'm going to ask the homestay owner
if they have a phone.

160
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,160
Don't.

161
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:05,520
If she sees a strange number calling
at a weird hour,

162
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,200
it'll become a huge deal.

163
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,200
Forget it.

164
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,680
At worst, I'll get scolded a little.

165
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:14,720
If I explain it nicely, it'll be fine.

166
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:26,680
Pie.

167
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,320
Let me ask you something.

168
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,560
With a mom that strict,

169
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:35,880
have you ever even had a boyfriend?

170
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:45,920
Well…

171
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:49,360
If I'm being honest…

172
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,200
- No?
- No.

173
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,480
You already knew. Why ask?

174
00:15:57,120 --> 00:16:00,640
Do you realize you're kind of a rare item?

175
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:03,680
Wait. Should I be happy about that?

176
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,240
Yes.

177
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:10,600
Thanks.

178
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:16,480
Good night.

179
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:18,960
Good night.

180
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,120
My dad fixed it for you.

181
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,400
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

182
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,920
- Alright.
- Thank you again.

183
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,120
- Thank you, Uncle. We'll get going now.
- Yes.

184
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,040
See you.

185
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:15,160
- Hello, Auntie.
- Where did you disappear to all night?

186
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:17,920
Pie's mom called and went off on me.

187
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:20,160
The bike had a flat tire.

188
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:22,800
It was already dark,
so we couldn't come down the mountain.

189
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,280
There was no signal either.

190
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:25,839
Where's Pie now?

191
00:17:26,599 --> 00:17:28,560
Right here. Want to talk to her?

192
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,160
Here.

193
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,520
Hello, Aunt Saen.

194
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:35,400
Pie, your mom called last night.
She sounded really worried.

195
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:37,680
She went off on me and gave me an earful.

196
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:40,040
Aunt Saen, I'm sorry about my mom.

197
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,080
<i>Yeah.</i>

198
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:42,800
Pie, come back soon,

199
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:45,400
and call your mom
to let her know you're safe.

200
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:47,920
I already told her not to worry.

201
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,840
I said my nephew was taking care of you.

202
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:53,000
<i>But she wouldn't listen to anything.</i>

203
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,760
<i>She's probably waiting for your call.</i>

204
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:57,920
Okay. I'm heading back right now.

205
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,560
Thank you so much.

206
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:02,400
We're heading back.

207
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:04,280
- <i>Make it quick.</i>
- Yeah.

208
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:05,400
Got it.

209
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:08,000
<i>I have errands today.</i>
<i>Watch the homestay for me.</i>

210
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,000
Sure.

211
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:10,720
Is something wrong?

212
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,040
Let's hurry back. Come on.

213
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,840
What?

214
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:36,640
Pie.

215
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:45,160
Hello, Krarok.
Where are you? Are you with Pie?

216
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,720
How are you calling back?

217
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,480
I thought there was no signal.

218
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:52,120
We split up to collect data
in different villages.

219
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,880
Her bike tire went flat,

220
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,680
so she couldn't get back in time.

221
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,440
She had to stay there overnight.

222
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:59,680
Why did she go with the owner's nephew?

223
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:00,800
Who is he?

224
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:03,920
Oh, he's just a ten-year-old boy.

225
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,920
He went as her interpreter.

226
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,920
There's nothing to worry about.

227
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,600
Where is Pie?
Why isn't she speaking to me herself?

228
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,680
She's probably on her way back now.

229
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:15,360
I can call
because I'm somewhere with signal.

230
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:18,200
I just wanted to report to you
so you wouldn't worry.

231
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:21,520
Maybe try calling Pie again.
I have to get back to work now.

232
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,640
I have to go. Goodbye.

233
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,760
Wait.

234
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:28,560
Oh my goodness, Pie.

235
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:31,160
How long can you keep this lie going?

236
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:39,680
- Hello.
- <i>Pie.</i>

237
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:41,160
Why are you answering yourself?

238
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,960
Doesn't the resort have an operator?

239
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:45,120
I happened to be by the phone.

240
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,440
I was just about to call you.

241
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,920
When it rang, I hurried to answer
because I thought it might be you.

242
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:54,000
Mom, I'm sorry I didn't call last night.

243
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,560
I went to another village for research.

244
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,640
The tire went flat on the way back.

245
00:19:57,720 --> 00:20:01,280
It was getting late, so I stayed.
It was dangerous.

246
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,760
Where's Krarok?

247
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:04,040
Were you together?

248
00:20:04,640 --> 00:20:07,240
She went to a different village.
We weren't together.

249
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,520
Why did you go with the owner's nephew?

250
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:14,680
He went as my interpreter.
He's a ten-year-old boy.

251
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:16,400
You're sure he's ten?

252
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,360
Yes.

253
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:20,600
If you don't believe me,
I'll take a picture with him.

254
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:23,680
No. If someone wants to lie,

255
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,480
they can take a picture with anyone.

256
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:28,840
<i>This time, I'll consider it unavoidable.</i>

257
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,400
But don't let it happen again, Pie.

258
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,760
If there's a next time,

259
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,160
I'll come up there myself.

260
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,160
Do you understand?

261
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:40,880
Yes, Mom. I understand.

262
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:43,280
I won't make you worry again.

263
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:55,120
Do you really think you can pull this off?

264
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:58,560
I'm sorry for dragging you into this mess.

265
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:02,400
It's fine. Friends help friends.

266
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:06,720
<i>But how long do you think</i>
<i>you can keep lying, Pie?</i>

267
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,280
Don't forget.

268
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:12,120
Once you lie once, you have to keep lying.

269
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:14,040
And when the lies pile up,

270
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:16,520
you won't even remember what you said.

271
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:19,760
<i>There are no real secrets in this world.</i>

272
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,600
I know.

273
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,920
I just need to finish my thesis.

274
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,280
Once I go back to Bangkok,
I won't have to lie anymore.

275
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:31,160
I'll tell Mom the truth about everything.

276
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:35,320
Thanks for helping me
and for keeping me in check.

277
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:41,240
But you're not lying to me, are you?

278
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:43,600
- About what?
- <i>That resort owner's nephew.</i>

279
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:45,240
The hill tribe kid you told me about.

280
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,840
He really is ten, right?

281
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:51,520
He's not actually some tall,
muscular mountain guy, is he?

282
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:54,360
If you want to know,
come see for yourself.

283
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:57,400
What's that supposed to mean?

284
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:59,000
That's suspicious already.

285
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:02,840
That's it. Phone bills cost money. Bye.

286
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,920
Seriously, Pie.

287
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,680
MUNGMINK

288
00:22:18,560 --> 00:22:20,480
Yes, Miss Mungmink?

289
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:22,880
How can your humble servant assist you?

290
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,880
About the thesis topic
we discussed before,

291
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:28,200
I made a list for you to look at.

292
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:30,160
Sure. Leave it there, Mink.

293
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:31,560
I'll take a look when I'm free.

294
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,120
- Rok.
- Hm?

295
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:36,680
Have you applied for any jobs yet?

296
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,440
Not yet. I'm scared to.

297
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:40,960
I want to survive my thesis first.

298
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:42,800
Why do you ask?

299
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,360
My secretary, Orn,
is going on maternity leave.

300
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,040
So I need a replacement.

301
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,680
I was thinking
of someone capable like you.

302
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,360
You interested?

303
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,760
I'm interested.

304
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:55,640
I can do everything Rok can.

305
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:58,160
Anything you need, I can do it.

306
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:01,440
But I probably wouldn't dare hire you.

307
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:06,040
Weren't you going into business
with your uncle after graduation?

308
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:09,080
Well, yes.

309
00:23:12,280 --> 00:23:15,080
Let's go, Mink. Pun needs to keep working.

310
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:17,080
We'll get going now. Goodbye.

311
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:21,200
Let's go.

312
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,160
- Rok.
- Yes?

313
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:29,840
I have to check on a hotel project
in Mae Hong Son.

314
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:30,840
Want to come with me?

315
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,720
You'd get to see Pie too.

316
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:36,400
Let's talk about that later, Pun. Bye.

317
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,680
Bye.

318
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:39,440
Come on. Let's go home.

319
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:42,640
Let's go. Let's go home.

320
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:00,800
- One, two, three.
- Hands off.

321
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:10,600
Did you lie about the weight?

322
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:13,080
I'm actually over the limit.
They wouldn't let me on!

323
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,080
Come on, get up here.

324
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:28,720
Win, you got blocked. Look!

325
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,280
- Want to go again?
- I'm good.

326
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:31,960
That was fun!

327
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:34,600
So good.

328
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:36,000
One, two, three.

329
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:37,080
Smile.

330
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:38,800
Oops, sorry.

331
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:40,200
I made a mess.

332
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:49,480
Pun. The other day, I ran into Uncle Dech.

333
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:52,560
He asked me to remind you
to take good care of Mink.

334
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,120
I know.

335
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:57,120
I just helped her with her thesis topic.

336
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,800
What do you think about her?

337
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:00,480
Are you interested at all?

338
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:03,920
I think, if you don't like anyone yet,

339
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:07,160
you should try seeing her.

340
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,480
Get to know her first.

341
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:09,600
There's no harm in that.

342
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:11,280
Yes, Mom.

343
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:12,800
Are you trying to set him up?

344
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:17,160
And what if I am?

345
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:19,120
Shouldn't you ask your son first?

346
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:21,400
I have full authority.
I don't need to ask.

347
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,240
Oh my goodness.

348
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,360
You can't eat it like that.

349
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:34,960
You have to split it in the middle.
It's hot inside.

350
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:36,920
Divide it into two like this.

351
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:40,280
Then spread the cream and jam.
Or jam first, then cream.

352
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:43,800
And if I want to eat it whole
without splitting it,

353
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,080
is that a problem?

354
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:46,600
You'll burn your mouth, of course.

355
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:49,320
At home, eat however you like,

356
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:52,160
but when you're out with my friends,
you have to eat properly.

357
00:25:52,240 --> 00:25:53,480
Otherwise, it's embarrassing.

358
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,240
Gosh, Sil!

359
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,560
Don't let the spoon hit the cup.

360
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:04,280
Leaving the spoon in like that,

361
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:06,480
if someone sees it,
they'll think you have no manners.

362
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:08,320
How many times do I have to tell you?

363
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,360
I've told you since we dated,
now our son's grown.

364
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:12,680
You still can't remember.

365
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:19,120
Where are you going?
You haven't finished eating.

366
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,800
I don't feel like it anymore.

367
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,040
I'm going for a walk.

368
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:24,800
Your father never does
anything the way I like.

369
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:26,240
I always have to nag him.

370
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:37,000
- Dad.
- What is it, Pun?

371
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:39,080
Seriously, how do you grow orchids?

372
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:40,600
Every one of yours blooms.

373
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,760
I tried before,
and not a single one survived.

374
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,400
It's not hard.

375
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:46,720
You just have to understand them.

376
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:48,080
Understand their nature.

377
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:50,760
Know how much sunlight they like,

378
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:53,760
how much humidity,
how much water they need.

379
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:58,680
If you force it
against its nature, it dies.

380
00:26:58,760 --> 00:26:59,760
That's normal.

381
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:06,000
And being with Mom,

382
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:08,680
are you forcing yourself?

383
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:15,960
Are you trying to comfort me?

384
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:19,800
Well.

385
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,240
Yes.

386
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:23,520
When you first courted Mom,

387
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:26,440
did you know she was this fussy?

388
00:27:28,240 --> 00:27:31,800
I did. She was always like this.

389
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:34,080
But back then,

390
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:37,800
she was prettier, so I overlooked it.

391
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:40,960
Now, you can see for yourself.

392
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,200
I've accepted my fate.

393
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:47,800
Hey.

394
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:49,560
Pun.

395
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:54,360
If you're going to choose
someone as your wife,

396
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:56,720
don't let beauty blind you.

397
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:58,080
You have to know her personality,

398
00:27:58,160 --> 00:28:00,240
whether you truly get along.

399
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:02,840
Like they say, you should be well matched.

400
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:06,480
In my opinion, choose a woman
who doesn't talk much, isn't demanding,

401
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:10,440
not picky, not nagging, and easygoing.

402
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:12,000
That kind of woman is best.

403
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:16,040
Otherwise, after marriage,
your wife turns into your mother.

404
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:18,720
Like the saying goes, right?

405
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:22,440
Women cry before marriage, men cry after.

406
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:24,800
Exactly!

407
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:29,640
You see, I even got a lesson
on how to drink tea properly.

408
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:33,240
It's just a pastry.
You put it in your mouth and that's it.

409
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:35,520
Why does it have to be so complicated?

410
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,200
It's so exhausting.

411
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,800
Aunt Saen!

412
00:28:45,880 --> 00:28:47,000
Aunt Saen.

413
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,560
I'd like to get a ride to Pang Ung.

414
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:52,120
Oh, sure. I'll call for you.

415
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:54,160
But it'll be a shared ride.

416
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:57,160
They'll pick up other passengers first,

417
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:59,400
then come get you at the scheduled time.

418
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:01,520
I see.

419
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:03,000
Why not just drive there?

420
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:03,960
Want me to drive you?

421
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:06,560
Really?

422
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:10,040
Won't you get carsick?

423
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:13,240
Only as a passenger.
When I'm driving, I'm fine.

424
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:15,320
So, what do you say?

425
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:16,480
Want me to go with you?

426
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:18,840
Of course.

427
00:29:19,480 --> 00:29:21,600
Aunt Saen, would you like to come with us?

428
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:22,640
I'll pass.

429
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:24,600
I went there often when I was young.

430
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:27,560
You two go together. And be careful.

431
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:29,600
Yes, Aunt Saen.

432
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:31,120
I'll go get my things ready then.

433
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:33,200
- Thank you.
- Alright.

434
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:39,120
Hey! Turn around.

435
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:43,160
If you're going just the two of you,
stay mindful.

436
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,360
Remember… Hey, listen!

437
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:46,120
Remember what I said.

438
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:47,840
Mindfulness is the most important thing.

439
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:53,240
Don't worry.
When I'm driving, I'm not dizzy at all.

440
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:55,560
Fully focused. No need to worry.

441
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:57,640
Hey, hey.

442
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,440
That's not what I meant.

443
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:02,920
I know.

444
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:06,840
You'd better.

445
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:41,480
It's so beautiful!

446
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:43,080
It really is.

447
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:47,600
What are you taking?

448
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:49,120
The view.

449
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:51,000
No, you're not. Let me see.

450
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:53,760
- It's the view.
- You're not. Let me see.

451
00:30:53,840 --> 00:30:54,760
- Seriously.
- Give it.

452
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:05,280
Need help?

453
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:08,880
No. I want to set up the tent by myself.

454
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:11,200
Who knows if I'll get
another chance to camp again.

455
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:12,960
Chance to set up a tent?

456
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:14,280
Yeah.

457
00:31:14,360 --> 00:31:15,440
How hard could it be?

458
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:18,800
If you knew my mom, you wouldn't say that.

459
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:21,640
Your mom's got tent issues?

460
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:23,440
Very funny.

461
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,160
Okay.

462
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:33,560
You good?

463
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,600
Wait a second.

464
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,800
Pie!

465
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:14,520
We have to finish setting up the tent

466
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:16,560
before it gets dark.

467
00:32:36,520 --> 00:32:38,040
Where is it?

468
00:32:38,920 --> 00:32:40,440
- Did you find it?
- Hold on.

469
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:45,560
Got it!

470
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:03,280
Ma'am, the phone.

471
00:33:06,760 --> 00:33:07,840
Hello?

472
00:33:08,440 --> 00:33:10,240
Mom, it's me.

473
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:11,840
Oh, Pie.

474
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,560
Why are you calling before the usual time?

475
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:14,640
Is something wrong?

476
00:33:14,720 --> 00:33:17,240
<i>Whose number are you calling from?</i>

477
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:19,440
It's a local number, Mom.

478
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:23,520
I dropped my phone in the water,
so I borrowed one to call you.

479
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:26,200
Why didn't you call
from the homestay's number?

480
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,160
I'm out in a village for work. It's far.

481
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:29,240
I might not be back by eight.

482
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:32,160
That sounds strange, Pie.

483
00:33:32,240 --> 00:33:35,880
Why are you working so late all the time?

484
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:39,520
<i>Next time, I'm not letting you</i>
<i>go anywhere alone again.</i>

485
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,920
Once our house renovations are finished,

486
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,640
I'll come see you right away.

487
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:44,760
Mom.

488
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:47,000
The work is almost done.

489
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:49,640
<i>Once it's finished,</i>
<i>I'll come back right away.</i>

490
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,320
Don't worry, okay?

491
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,600
Bye, Mom.

492
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:54,000
<i>Alright.</i>

493
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:08,679
I've never seen this many stars before.

494
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:10,840
Totally worth the effort.

495
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:15,760
Something better is coming.

496
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:17,960
Like what?

497
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:20,239
Tonight,

498
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:24,400
Comet Wirtanen's visible,
only every five and a half years.

499
00:34:25,719 --> 00:34:26,880
Really?

500
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:30,320
So if we miss it, we have to wait
another five and a half years?

501
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,120
Yeah.

502
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:38,199
Comets are strange.

503
00:34:39,880 --> 00:34:42,239
They pass by for us to see, then leave.

504
00:34:44,719 --> 00:34:46,639
Some never come back.

505
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:49,960
Some return and cross our paths again.

506
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,440
Just like people.

507
00:34:58,160 --> 00:35:01,720
Some keep coming back into our lives.

508
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:05,160
Some cross our paths once

509
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:07,000
and never again.

510
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:11,640
But there's one difference.

511
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:16,920
With comets,

512
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:21,560
astronomers can calculate
when they'll return.

513
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:23,800
But with people,

514
00:35:24,560 --> 00:35:27,200
we never know when we'll meet again.

515
00:35:33,080 --> 00:35:34,640
When you think about it, it's amazing.

516
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:38,080
The fact that people get to meet at all.

517
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:45,760
That's why they say,

518
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:48,640
if you want to do something, just do it.

519
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:50,960
Enjoy life.

520
00:35:52,720 --> 00:35:54,080
If you keep waiting,

521
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:57,840
you might miss your chance forever.

522
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,760
Because we never really know

523
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:05,680
when goodbye

524
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:08,200
will come.

525
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:17,240
We see each other in the morning,

526
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:22,480
and by evening, we might part forever.

527
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,080
I'm sorry.

528
00:37:29,240 --> 00:37:30,720
It's really a miracle.

529
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,480
What?

530
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:40,920
The comet?

531
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,240
Pie.

532
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,600
You're the miracle in my life.

533
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:18,040
PUN

534
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:21,840
That sharp-tongued mom
must be calling for her daughter again.

535
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:25,720
Hello, Saensuk Homestay.

536
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:29,200
Aunt Saen.

537
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:30,520
It's me, Pun.

538
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:32,800
Are you upset about something?

539
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:37,760
Sorry, Pun. I thought it was
that bossy mom of my customer.

540
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,040
<i>What's up?</i>

541
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:40,520
Well.

542
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:42,800
I tried calling Koh,
but he didn't pick up.

543
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:44,640
I'm not sure if something's wrong.

544
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:48,200
Your little Patongkoh is out
taking customers on a trip.

545
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:51,760
Koh, the guy who slept
with a bottle for a month is going out?

546
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:54,960
His condition's much better now.

547
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:57,960
That's a relief.

548
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:02,160
I dragged him up to you,
thought he'd just keep drinking there.

549
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:04,720
Hearing this makes me feel better.

550
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:10,240
Please tell him
the stuff he packed at the old house,

551
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:12,160
I've had someone move it already.

552
00:40:12,240 --> 00:40:15,000
I'll take care of it.
He can come by when he's ready.

553
00:40:15,080 --> 00:40:17,840
Thank you so much
for always being there for him.

554
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:21,920
I'm his aunt and still
couldn't help him this much.

555
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:25,280
Win doesn't have any siblings.

556
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:27,400
You're like his real older brother.

557
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:29,720
I don't have a younger sibling either.

558
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:32,080
He's like a real little brother to me too.

559
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:33,880
Aunt Saen.

560
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:37,120
I might have work in Mae Hong Son soon.

561
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:40,320
If I go, I'll stop by to visit.

562
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:42,640
Please do! You're more than welcome.

563
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:46,160
Win will be so happy
his beloved big brother's coming.

564
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:47,600
Of course. Oh, right.

565
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:50,280
About the scholarship to study in Japan,

566
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:52,600
I think there might be good news soon.

567
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:54,280
I'll update you right away.

568
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:03,120
<i>Where is Pie staying?</i>

569
00:41:06,240 --> 00:41:07,920
<i>This is a secret, okay?</i>

570
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,880
You can't tell anyone where I am.

571
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,280
Don't let this get out. Got it?

572
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:13,720
Zipping my lips.

573
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:19,440
I keep my promises. Sorry, Pun.

574
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:25,440
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>If I'm going to see her, I'll ask.</i>

575
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:28,560
You little Krarok.

576
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:33,200
Double rainbow!

577
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:40,840
It's beautiful.

578
00:43:08,680 --> 00:43:11,600
For something this beautiful
to mean death,

579
00:43:12,560 --> 00:43:13,920
isn't that a bit cruel?

580
00:43:15,560 --> 00:43:18,760
I'm not being cruel.
It's just an old legend.

581
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:21,160
Then what I believe must be right.

582
00:43:22,040 --> 00:43:23,640
A double rainbow means love.

583
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:26,720
Lovers will find their way back.

584
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:29,480
Just like us.

585
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:46,160
Pie.

586
00:43:48,840 --> 00:43:50,160
Do you know

587
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:53,120
you saved my life?

588
00:43:59,520 --> 00:44:00,640
Before this,

589
00:44:02,720 --> 00:44:04,880
I thought I had no one left.

590
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:11,000
After my parents died,

591
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:13,520
I sold the house.

592
00:44:14,280 --> 00:44:15,200
Nothing left.

593
00:44:19,480 --> 00:44:21,440
Sometimes I even thought,

594
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:28,160
if I'd been in that car with them,

595
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:30,880
maybe it would've been better.

596
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:36,400
But you changed my mind.

597
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:40,840
You made me feel like…

598
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:45,040
life isn't over.

599
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:53,680
You gave me

600
00:44:56,240 --> 00:44:58,120
a reason to keep living.

601
00:45:04,080 --> 00:45:05,760
If I helped you find

602
00:45:06,760 --> 00:45:08,760
a reason to live,

603
00:45:10,720 --> 00:45:12,120
you helped me understand

604
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:15,520
what life really is.

605
00:45:27,480 --> 00:45:28,680
Before this,

606
00:45:30,440 --> 00:45:31,720
I was like a robot.

607
00:45:33,360 --> 00:45:35,840
I just followed whatever
my mom programmed.

608
00:45:37,680 --> 00:45:38,960
But you gave me freedom,

609
00:45:40,080 --> 00:45:41,240
courage,

610
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:47,280
confidence to do things
I never dared to do.

611
00:45:55,680 --> 00:45:57,240
I'm glad we met, Win.

612
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:10,440
Maybe we met by coincidence.

613
00:46:15,760 --> 00:46:17,600
But we'll stay together long enough

614
00:46:19,920 --> 00:46:21,360
for it to become destiny.

615
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:27,040
Then,

616
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:30,960
let's stay together long enough

617
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:33,440
for it to become destiny.

618
00:46:57,680 --> 00:47:00,440
Damn it, Win.

619
00:47:10,520 --> 00:47:12,600
MISSED CALL, PUN

620
00:47:20,120 --> 00:47:21,800
Damn, Koh.

621
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:24,080
Took you long enough to call me.

622
00:47:24,160 --> 00:47:26,240
Too busy taking care
of your customer all night?

623
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:28,960
Hey, how'd you know?

624
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:30,760
Aunt Saen told you, right?

625
00:47:30,840 --> 00:47:31,760
<i>Yeah.</i>

626
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:34,240
She said you're doing much better.

627
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:36,680
Where'd you find that cure?

628
00:47:37,760 --> 00:47:39,560
Around here.

629
00:47:39,640 --> 00:47:42,160
Around here means a place or a person?

630
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:46,160
If you want to know,
you'll have to come see for yourself.

631
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:48,840
Don't challenge me. I'm definitely going.

632
00:47:49,360 --> 00:47:51,240
Might have work in Mae Hong Son soon.

633
00:47:51,320 --> 00:47:52,880
I'll see it with my own eyes.

634
00:47:54,360 --> 00:47:57,760
Sure, Pun. I'll introduce you
to the miracle cure.

635
00:47:58,360 --> 00:48:01,080
Alright. If I head up there,
I'll let you know.

636
00:48:02,200 --> 00:48:03,400
Hey, Koh.

637
00:48:03,480 --> 00:48:06,640
Gotta go. I need to grab food
before a meeting.

638
00:48:06,720 --> 00:48:08,560
- Talk later.
- <i>Hang on.</i>

639
00:48:09,400 --> 00:48:12,240
- What?
- <i>You're a miracle cure for me too.</i>

640
00:48:13,320 --> 00:48:16,160
If it weren't for you,
my life would've fallen apart.

641
00:48:16,920 --> 00:48:17,920
Thank you, Pun.

642
00:48:19,680 --> 00:48:22,200
If my brother falls, I help.
That's normal.

643
00:48:22,280 --> 00:48:23,680
<i>Don't overthink it.</i>

644
00:48:23,760 --> 00:48:24,880
Bye.

645
00:48:39,840 --> 00:48:41,840
Is Pang Ung as beautiful as you imagined?

646
00:48:43,040 --> 00:48:45,920
- Hello. How did you get here?
- Hi.

647
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:49,840
A friend of mine was coming here,
so I hitched a ride.

648
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:51,480
I brought you breakfast.

649
00:48:51,560 --> 00:48:53,760
- Thank you so much.
- No worries.

650
00:48:53,840 --> 00:48:55,600
Northern pork blood rice
and grilled chicken.

651
00:48:55,680 --> 00:48:57,040
Have some first.

652
00:48:57,120 --> 00:49:00,320
Around noon, I'll take you
to Ban Rak Thai for Yunnan pork leg.

653
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:01,280
It's nearby.

654
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:03,480
Okay, I was just wanting to go there.

655
00:49:03,560 --> 00:49:04,520
Good.

656
00:49:04,600 --> 00:49:06,400
Thank you so much.

657
00:49:07,240 --> 00:49:08,400
Oh, Auntie.

658
00:49:08,480 --> 00:49:10,880
Win, Aunt Saen brought us food.

659
00:49:10,960 --> 00:49:12,760
Guess we don't need instant porridge.

660
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:15,960
Hey, Win, where did you park?

661
00:49:16,040 --> 00:49:18,880
I need my water bottle.
It might be in the car.

662
00:49:19,520 --> 00:49:20,880
Over there.

663
00:49:20,960 --> 00:49:22,240
I'll get it for you.

664
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:23,280
Alright.

665
00:49:32,440 --> 00:49:33,680
Here you go, Auntie.

666
00:49:34,320 --> 00:49:35,440
Thanks.

667
00:49:36,240 --> 00:49:37,200
Hey.

668
00:49:37,280 --> 00:49:40,760
Pun called last night.
He said he couldn't reach you.

669
00:49:41,360 --> 00:49:42,640
I know.

670
00:49:42,720 --> 00:49:43,840
I talked to him this morning.

671
00:49:44,680 --> 00:49:47,160
Then why didn't you answer him last night?

672
00:49:47,240 --> 00:49:48,720
What were you busy doing?

673
00:49:50,440 --> 00:49:51,320
Hey.

674
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:53,800
You've already gone that far with Pie?

675
00:49:54,760 --> 00:49:55,960
Far enough.

676
00:49:58,040 --> 00:49:58,960
Win, you brat!

677
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:01,240
Do you even realize what you've done?

678
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:02,920
I do.

679
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:06,520
Pie isn't like those girls
you used to casually date.

680
00:50:06,600 --> 00:50:08,400
Those girls you used to fool around with,

681
00:50:08,480 --> 00:50:10,280
they were all bold and fiery.

682
00:50:10,360 --> 00:50:12,800
They wouldn't mind. But Pie's different.

683
00:50:12,880 --> 00:50:14,920
You know how protective her mom is.

684
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:16,440
I know, Auntie.

685
00:50:17,080 --> 00:50:20,000
I'm not playing around.
I'm serious about her.

686
00:50:21,160 --> 00:50:23,160
Are you sure you really like her?

687
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:26,440
Not just because you're going
through something

688
00:50:26,520 --> 00:50:29,160
and got carried away when you met her?

689
00:50:30,840 --> 00:50:33,280
Auntie, I'm not a kid anymore.

690
00:50:34,560 --> 00:50:36,560
I've had a lot of girlfriends,
that's true.

691
00:50:36,640 --> 00:50:38,800
But this time, I know it's different.

692
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:42,200
Pie gives me hope.

693
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:46,720
She makes me want to become
a better version of myself for her.

694
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:52,800
If her demanding mother finds out,
there'll be trouble.

695
00:50:52,880 --> 00:50:55,000
It won't be as easy as you think.

696
00:50:55,080 --> 00:50:56,520
Prepare yourself.

697
00:50:56,600 --> 00:50:58,440
I'm confident we'll get through it.

698
00:50:59,800 --> 00:51:01,000
I'll do my best.

699
00:51:07,480 --> 00:51:08,800
Pun!

700
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:09,840
- Pun!
- What?

701
00:51:09,920 --> 00:51:11,120
Pack your bags.

702
00:51:11,200 --> 00:51:13,000
The client approved.

703
00:51:13,080 --> 00:51:14,200
The contract is signed.

704
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:17,320
We can start right away.

705
00:51:17,400 --> 00:51:18,720
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

706
00:51:18,800 --> 00:51:20,360
Guess I'm finally getting Northern food.

707
00:51:21,360 --> 00:51:22,800
Not that project.

708
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:25,160
Mae Hong Son Museum went to another firm.

709
00:51:25,240 --> 00:51:28,880
But we got Chumphon instead.

710
00:51:28,960 --> 00:51:29,880
What?

711
00:51:30,840 --> 00:51:32,480
Hey, Win.

712
00:51:32,560 --> 00:51:36,080
Turns out I got a job in the South.
Not going up there after all.

713
00:51:36,160 --> 00:51:37,880
Guess I won't get to see
your miracle cure.

714
00:51:38,440 --> 00:51:39,400
<i>It's fine, Pun.</i>

715
00:51:39,480 --> 00:51:42,160
I'll bring the miracle cure
to you instead.

716
00:51:42,240 --> 00:51:44,040
Talking that boldly,

717
00:51:44,600 --> 00:51:45,880
so this one's serious?

718
00:51:46,720 --> 00:51:48,280
Or just another fling?

719
00:51:48,880 --> 00:51:51,720
No, this one's serious.

720
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:56,360
She's the one who gave me hope.

721
00:51:57,280 --> 00:51:58,360
Alright.

722
00:51:58,440 --> 00:51:59,640
Good to hear you're serious.

723
00:52:00,640 --> 00:52:02,480
We'll meet when you're back in Bangkok.

724
00:52:03,720 --> 00:52:04,680
Sure.

725
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:17,000
Here?

726
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:19,720
I don't know.
Do you even know how to massage?

727
00:52:23,880 --> 00:52:25,000
Win.

728
00:52:25,080 --> 00:52:27,760
I haven't washed my hair yet.
Does it smell?

729
00:52:28,400 --> 00:52:29,400
Smells great.

730
00:52:30,080 --> 00:52:31,560
Really? Smell it.

731
00:52:33,320 --> 00:52:35,680
- Feeling better?
- Much better.

732
00:52:36,480 --> 00:52:37,440
Pie!

733
00:52:37,520 --> 00:52:39,240
- Yes?
- Your mom called.

734
00:52:39,320 --> 00:52:40,560
Oh, okay.

735
00:52:41,320 --> 00:52:42,360
Be right back.

736
00:52:44,120 --> 00:52:45,880
- Thank you, Aunt Saen.
- Sure.

737
00:52:48,200 --> 00:52:49,160
This is too much.

738
00:52:49,760 --> 00:52:51,400
Way too much.

739
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:53,320
What? I'm just encouraging my girlfriend.

740
00:52:53,400 --> 00:52:54,800
Not bothering anyone.

741
00:52:55,480 --> 00:52:57,840
You've never met her mom.
You got a death wish?

742
00:52:57,920 --> 00:52:59,920
I'll lock the phone for you, okay?

743
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:01,440
So you don't have to walk.

744
00:53:02,120 --> 00:53:03,160
I'll handle it.

745
00:53:03,240 --> 00:53:04,920
You really do have a death wish.

746
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:07,040
- Wait till her mom shows up, you'll see.
- What?

747
00:53:07,120 --> 00:53:09,080
- You stay here.
- Yeah.

748
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:14,840
No need to come, Mom.

749
00:53:14,920 --> 00:53:17,680
You'd just waste time waiting.

750
00:53:17,760 --> 00:53:19,640
I'm rushing this project like crazy.

751
00:53:19,720 --> 00:53:21,400
Once I'm done, I'll come back.

752
00:53:22,360 --> 00:53:24,040
I'm only working.

753
00:53:24,120 --> 00:53:25,960
No one's hitting on me.

754
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:30,720
Mom, I've got to get back to work.

755
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:32,400
I'll finish and head home soon.

756
00:53:33,440 --> 00:53:35,040
Yes, Mom.

757
00:53:35,120 --> 00:53:38,480
Okay. Sure. Bye.

758
00:53:46,480 --> 00:53:48,160
If your mom found out about us,

759
00:53:49,120 --> 00:53:50,400
what would she say?

760
00:53:52,080 --> 00:53:53,560
I don't know.

761
00:53:55,160 --> 00:53:56,320
Probably…

762
00:53:58,360 --> 00:53:59,680
She'll probably be shocked.

763
00:54:00,640 --> 00:54:02,600
Better not let her know yet.

764
00:54:07,320 --> 00:54:08,920
What kind of guy

765
00:54:09,800 --> 00:54:11,280
would she accept?

766
00:54:15,040 --> 00:54:18,400
I don't know. I've never asked.

767
00:54:21,120 --> 00:54:24,160
If we ever have to tell her,

768
00:54:24,240 --> 00:54:26,000
we'll think about it then.

769
00:54:27,320 --> 00:54:28,320
Okay?

770
00:54:30,640 --> 00:54:31,920
Smile.

771
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:37,720
I need to get back to work.

772
00:54:38,680 --> 00:54:39,600
Smile.

773
00:55:00,120 --> 00:55:03,560
Life is like weaving cloth.

774
00:55:04,320 --> 00:55:07,160
Each of us is a single thread.

775
00:55:07,240 --> 00:55:12,120
But one thread alone
can't create a pattern.

776
00:55:12,200 --> 00:55:15,760
It has to intertwine with others.

777
00:55:15,840 --> 00:55:19,280
Whether it's destined by merit or karma.

778
00:55:20,960 --> 00:55:25,840
If it's a soulmate,
meeting brings happiness.

779
00:55:25,920 --> 00:55:28,600
They support each other
into a beautiful pattern.

780
00:55:28,680 --> 00:55:30,840
But if it's karmic entanglement,

781
00:55:30,920 --> 00:55:34,800
they get tangled into something messy.

782
00:55:34,880 --> 00:55:35,920
Don't you think so?

783
00:55:40,560 --> 00:55:41,440
Mink!

784
00:55:42,680 --> 00:55:43,520
Yes?

785
00:55:43,600 --> 00:55:45,960
I talked all that time.
Were you listening?

786
00:55:46,560 --> 00:55:48,640
Nope. I'm busy.

787
00:55:48,720 --> 00:55:51,480
Tomorrow's my birthday.
I haven't finalized plans with my friends.

788
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:53,560
What?

789
00:55:54,720 --> 00:55:56,720
Since when do birthdays need a briefing?

790
00:55:57,720 --> 00:55:58,960
Of course they do.

791
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:00,920
I want it perfect.

792
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:04,080
You only turn 22 once.

793
00:56:04,160 --> 00:56:05,920
Suit yourself.

794
00:56:10,080 --> 00:56:13,680
<i>White or flamingo pink theme</i>
<i>for my birthday.</i>

795
00:56:13,760 --> 00:56:16,720
<i>The party starts at 3 p.m.</i>
<i>No gifts needed.</i>

796
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:18,400
<i>Just come and party.</i>

797
00:56:18,480 --> 00:56:20,040
<i>Photographer and props are ready.</i>

798
00:56:20,120 --> 00:56:21,360
<i>If you take your own photos,</i>

799
00:56:21,440 --> 00:56:24,040
<i>send them to me before posting,</i>

800
00:56:24,120 --> 00:56:24,960
<i>for maximum slay.</i>

801
00:56:25,040 --> 00:56:26,240
Hang on.

802
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:27,840
Photos on social media?

803
00:56:27,920 --> 00:56:29,560
That'll blow everything.

804
00:56:30,720 --> 00:56:32,080
Pie's mom will definitely see.

805
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:36,240
<i>I can't come, sorry.</i>

806
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:40,880
Mink!

807
00:56:42,360 --> 00:56:43,240
What's up?

808
00:56:43,320 --> 00:56:45,360
Why aren't you coming?

809
00:56:45,440 --> 00:56:47,680
I'm not feeling well.

810
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:51,800
I can't party.
Don't want to spread germs to you.

811
00:56:54,240 --> 00:56:55,400
That's annoying.

812
00:56:55,480 --> 00:56:57,800
Will anyone else be coming?
No one's responding.

813
00:56:57,880 --> 00:57:01,160
Probably busy with projects.
They'll reply soon.

814
00:57:03,400 --> 00:57:05,120
Happy early birthday, though.

815
00:57:05,720 --> 00:57:07,960
Thanks. Catch you later.

816
00:57:08,040 --> 00:57:08,960
Bye.

817
00:57:22,240 --> 00:57:23,480
SATURDAY, 8 DECEMBER

818
00:57:38,560 --> 00:57:40,440
<i>Hey, are you going to Mink's party?</i>

819
00:57:40,520 --> 00:57:43,240
<i>No, she's too much. Too fussy.</i>

820
00:57:43,320 --> 00:57:45,320
<i>Hey, wrong group chat.</i>

821
00:57:49,720 --> 00:57:50,760
Forget it!

822
00:57:50,840 --> 00:57:52,880
No one's coming. Just go home.

823
00:57:52,960 --> 00:57:55,800
Okay, I'll upload the photos
to the Cloud for you.

824
00:57:55,880 --> 00:57:58,160
Just throw them away.
I don't want them anymore.

825
00:58:12,560 --> 00:58:13,680
Happy birthday.

826
00:58:14,760 --> 00:58:15,960
Start acting your age now.

827
00:58:20,320 --> 00:58:22,240
When did Krarok get back
from Mae Hong Son?

828
00:58:22,320 --> 00:58:25,160
<i>Miss Krarok hasn't left.</i>
<i>She's been in Bangkok.</i>

829
00:58:25,240 --> 00:58:26,640
Krarok!

830
00:58:26,720 --> 00:58:29,000
Win, you're back?

831
00:58:35,280 --> 00:58:36,400
Mom.

832
00:58:36,480 --> 00:58:38,120
Pack your things and go home now!

833
00:58:38,200 --> 00:58:39,760
- Pie!
- Mom.

834
00:58:39,840 --> 00:58:41,080
Pie!

835
00:58:41,160 --> 00:58:42,760
Ma'am, please stop.

836
00:58:43,960 --> 00:58:47,280
Get out of my face
and leave my daughter alone!

837
00:58:47,360 --> 00:58:48,440
Please, give me a chance.

838
00:59:15,720 --> 00:59:18,440
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
